line grid to lay out text.\n"},{"__typename":"DatoCmsParagraph","id":"DatoCmsParagraph-5645504-en","paragraphContent":"Alternatively, you can choose not to use the grid and manually measure from the cap height (as shown in the gif below), but it would require zooming all the way in and out of the pixel grid. Plus, the size of the container that holds your text might not be a multiple of 4px.\n"}]},"allDatoCmsArticle":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645977-en","title":"Things nobody ever taught me about CSS"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645476-en","title":"The 4px baseline grid - the present"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645505-en","title":"Recoil.js — The New, Better State Management Library for React"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-4700456-en","title":"Goodbye, Object Oriented Programming"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645416-en","title":"7 Alternatives to the <div> HTML Tag"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-4704245-en","title":"The perfect trip Norway"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645986-en","title":"What Are Articles?"}},{"node":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-4701495-en","title":"15 App Ideas to Build and Level Up your Coding Skills"}}]}},"pageContext":{"id":"DatoCmsArticle-5645505-en"}}}